  "text": "Drug treatments can have serious effects on oral status. The oral cavity harbours a variety of bacteria that do not normally cause problems [CITATION_1] . However, certain drug treatments such as antibiotics and chemotherapy can cause resident microflora to become pathological, which can increase the risk of systemic infection which occurs secondary to oral infection [CITATION_2] .",
